data.enText: to put a drug or other substance into a person's or an animal's body using a syringe

data.chText: 往肌肉里注射了肾上腺素。
data.enText: Adrenalin was injected into the muscle.

data.chText: 她从16岁起就开始自行注射胰岛素。
data.enText: She has been injecting herself with insulin since the age of 16.
to put a liquid into sth using a syringe or similar instrument

data.chText: 水果注入了化学药品以防腐坏。
data.enText: Chemicals are injected into the fruit to reduce decay.

data.chText: 水果注入了化学药品以防腐坏。
data.enText: The fruit is injected with chemicals to reduce decay.
to add a particular quality to sth

data.chText: 他的发言给整个活动增添了一丝幽默的气氛。
data.enText: His comments injected a note of humour into the proceedings.
to give money to an organization, a project, etc. so that it can function

data.chText: 他们拒绝对这一产业投入更多的资金。
data.enText: They are refusing to inject any more capital into the industry.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 向内 + ject 投掷，扔 → 向里面扔 → 注射

example: We injected the glucose into the patient's vein

tr: to introduce (a new aspect or element)
example: He injected new life into the performance

tr: force or drive (a fluid or gas) into by piercing

value.def: To inject someone with a substance such as a medicine means to put it into their body using a device with a needle called a syringe.

example.ex: His son was injected with strong drugs...
example.tran: 他儿子被注射了烈性麻醉药。

example.ex: The technique consists of injecting healthy cells into the weakened muscles...
example.tran: 该技术是把健康细胞注射到衰弱的肌肉里面。

example.ex: He needs to inject himself once a month.
example.tran: 他需要每月为自己打一针。

gramarinfo.label: Also V n, V n <l>with</l> n

value.def: If you inject a new, exciting, or interesting quality into a situation, you add it.

example.ex: She kept trying to inject a little fun into their relationship...
example.tran: 她一直在设法为他们的关系增添一些情趣。

example.ex: The result might inject more sense into future bargaining.
example.tran: 其结果可能为未来的谈判注入更多的理性。

value.def: If you inject money or resources into a business or organization, you provide more money or resources for it.

example.ex: He has injected £5.6 billion into the health service.
example.tran: 他已经为公共医疗卫生服务投入了 56 亿英镑。
